# Grassroot Hopper — Project Context

## What this is

Grassroot Hopper is a cooperative, open-source movement where any community on the planet can set up its own hub. You join through a community you already belong to (dance scene, art collective, dog park), scan a QR code, say a secret password spoken in person, and discover the hidden creative lives of the people you already know.

The founder is Julien, based in Brussels. The legal entity is GPFC srl. The first community is Lindy Hop Brussels.

## Repo structure

```
SPEC.md              — the source of truth (vision, principles, features, strategy)
ROADMAP.md           — technical & admin timeline, subsidies, legal structure
STATUS.md            — current project phase and decisions
CREATOR-SPEECH.md    — the creator pitch (café conversation format)
LAUNCH-SPEECH.md     — the reader pitch (event speech format)
website/index.html   — the live pitch deck site (static, no build tools)
.github/workflows/   — GitHub Pages deployment
```

## Non-negotiable constraints

These are core principles. Never suggest changes that violate them:

- **No comments, no likes, no DMs, no reactions. Ever.** Feedback happens in person.
- **No payments on the platform.** Business happens between humans.
- **Community-first entry.** QR code + secret password spoken in person. No browse, no discover page.
- **Cooperative ownership.** Each city is a cooperative (SC). Members vote by role.
- **Open source. Aggregate, don't build.** If someone built a great tool, integrate it.
- **No money flow through the platform.** The cooperative advises on tools but doesn't handle transactions.

## Tone of voice

Warm, direct, slightly rebellious. Anti-corporate but not angry. "Your neighbor who has a crazy idea and you believe them." Never corporate jargon, never startup-speak.

## Domains

grassroothopper.com, .org, .eu, .be — all owned.

## Key rule

Always read SPEC.md before making significant changes. It's the source of truth.
